Note: Runa Standard Library - Comprehensive Cryptography Module Tests
This test suite validates all cryptographic modules including hash functions,
AEAD encryption, asymmetric cryptography, PBKDF, signatures, PQC, JWT, and certificates.

Provides comprehensive coverage of security functionality, error handling,
performance characteristics, and standards compliance for production use.
:End Note

Import "crypto/hash" as hash
Import "crypto/aead" as aead
Import "crypto/symmetric" as symmetric
Import "crypto/tls" as tls
Import "crypto/zkp" as zkp
Import "crypto/asymmetric" as asymmetric
Import "crypto/pbkdf" as pbkdf
Import "crypto/signatures" as signatures
Import "crypto/pqc" as pqc
Import "crypto/jwt" as jwt
Import "crypto/certificates" as certificates
Import "crypto/exchange" as exchange
Import "crypto/primitives/random" as random
Import "crypto/primitives/bignum" as bignum
Import "crypto/primitives/curve" as curve
Import "crypto/primitives/field" as field
Import "testing" as testing

Note: Test Result Types

Type CryptoTestResult is Dictionary with:
    test_name as String
    passed as Boolean
    error_message as Optional[String]
    execution_time_ms as Integer
    details as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CryptoTestSuite is Dictionary with:
    suite_name as String
    total_tests as Integer
    passed_tests as Integer
    failed_tests as Integer
    results as List[CryptoTestResult]
    execution_time_ms as Integer

Note: Primary Test Functions

Process called "run_all_crypto_tests" returns CryptoTestSuite:
    Note: Execute comprehensive crypto test suite covering all modules
    Try:
        Let start_time be time.now
        Let all_results be empty list
        
        Note: Test each crypto module
        Let hash_results be test_hash_functions()
        Let aead_results be test_aead_encryption()
        Let symmetric_results be test_symmetric_encryption()
        Let tls_results be test_tls_protocol()
        Let zkp_results be test_zkp_systems()
        Let asymmetric_results be test_asymmetric_crypto()
        Let pbkdf_results be test_pbkdf_functions()
        Let signature_results be test_signature_schemes()
        Let pqc_results be test_post_quantum_crypto()
        Let jwt_results be test_jwt_operations()
        Let certificate_results be test_certificate_management()
        Let exchange_results be test_key_exchange()
        Let primitives_results be test_crypto_primitives()
        Let integration_results be test_crypto_integration()
        
        Note: Combine all results
        Set all_results to concatenate_lists with lists as list containing:
            hash_results, aead_results, symmetric_results, tls_results, zkp_results, asymmetric_results, pbkdf_results,
            signature_results, pqc_results, jwt_results, certificate_results,
            exchange_results, primitives_results, integration_results
        
        Let end_time be time.now
        Let total_time be time.difference_milliseconds with start_time as start_time and end_time as end_time
        
        Note: Calculate summary statistics
        Let total_tests be length of all_results
        Let passed_tests be count_passed_tests with results as all_results
        Let failed_tests be total_tests minus passed_tests
        
        Let test_suite be CryptoTestSuite with:
            suite_name as "Comprehensive Crypto Test Suite"
            total_tests as total_tests
            passed_tests as passed_tests
            failed_tests as failed_tests
            results as all_results
            execution_time_ms as total_time
        
        Return test_suite
    
    Catch error:
        Return create_error_test_suite with error_message as ("Test suite execution failed: " plus error as String)

